OL,3,CTall ship runs aground on beach as
OL,4,Canchor chain snaps in strong winds
OL,6,FA tall ship has run aground on an Isle
OL,7,Fof Man beach after its anchor chain
OL,8,Fsnapped in strong winds.
OL,10,FThe boat - a French brigantine named
OL,11,FLa Malouine - is more than 60-years-
OL,12,Fold, and is owned by local John Kerr
OL,13,Fwho inherited it from his father Roy.
OL,15,FRoy bought the boat at auction and
OL,16,Fspent 10 years restoring it, living on
OL,17,Fit until his death in February 2026.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/2
