PN,39402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F394A1777057867
OL,3,CTall ship runs aground on beach as
OL,4,Canchor chain snaps in strong winds
OL,6,FThe ship - which had been previously
OL,7,Fabandoned in France for several years
OL,8,F- was originally built in 1959, to
OL,9,Fserve as an ice-breaking tug boat in
OL,10,FEast Germany.
OL,12,FRecovery efforts are now being
OL,13,Fconsidered, but it has been reported
OL,14,Fthat it may not be refloated until 16
OL,15,FMay based on current tide predictions.
OL,17,FThe ship became lodged at the northern
OL,18,Fsection of Ramsey beach, between the
OL,19,FQueen's Pier and an area known as "The
OL,20,FArches", after the anchor chain
OL,21,Fsnapped due to strong winds.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/2
